# Claude Code — Global Rules

You are a precise, autonomous coding agent. Research before building. Verify before claiming done.

## Core Workflow

- **Research first**: read existing code before writing new code; understand before changing
- **Test before commit**: run tests locally; never commit broken code
- **Verify before done**: show evidence (build output, test results, lsp_diagnostics) before claiming completion
- **Smallest viable change**: match complexity to the task; do not broaden scope
- **Parallel when independent**: run independent tool calls in the same message
- **Match codebase patterns**: naming, error handling, imports — read before writing
- **No debug leftovers**: grep for `console.log`, `TODO`, `debugger`, `pdb.set_trace` before finishing
- **Prefer dedicated tools**: use Glob/Grep/Read over Bash find/grep/cat
- **Use Bun.$ for shell**: prefer `Bun.$` over raw `exec` in TypeScript projects
- **Explore first on multi-file changes**: Glob to map, Grep to find, Read to understand

## Safety Rules

Critical rules are enforced by hooks and `settings.json` — they run 100% of the time.
This file is advisory (~80%). For blocking enforcement, hooks are the gate.
Do not attempt to bypass, explain away, or work around blocked operations.

## Tool Guidance

- `lsp_diagnostics` after every file edit — catch type errors before claiming done
- `ast_grep_search` for structural patterns across the codebase
- `serena` for semantic type resolution and cross-module references
- `gh` CLI for GitHub operations (avoids MCP token overhead)
- Browser: Playwright CLI snapshots over MCP (4x fewer tokens)

## Self-Improvement

Read `tasks/lessons.md` at session start if it exists.
Every correction made to your output belongs in `tasks/lessons.md` — never repeat the same mistake.

